page.title: 03Trees in Catterick Garrison.
page.content: We surveyed the trees in this area, which is mainly woodland, and found that pine trees were most dominant with many of them growing in regular formation. The rest of the trees were randomly situated near the pines or used to form boundaries or hedges. There were a great many spruce, ash, sycamore, hawthorn, holly and larch. There were several silver birch, hazel, willow, horse-chestnut, wild rose, crab-apple and elderberry. Of beech, elm and lime, there were very few. We did not take particular note of trees growing in private gardens, but did note that there was quite a variety, including laburnum, privet, birch and poplar.
